election_record.label: New York 1810 State Senate, Western District

overview.note: Stephen Close, Elijah Durkee, Ebenezer Hunt, Robert Burch, Hosea Nelson, Christopher Bellinger, Oliver Collins, Uri Doolittle, Samuel Wetmore, Henry Wagner, John Billins, Christopher P. Billings, Reuben Hart, Septimus Evans, Stephen Phelps, Asahel Warner and Hugh MacNair were all Assembly candidates. Jonas Platt was a candidate for Governor. Reuben Smith, Roaben Smith, Freegift Thompson, Wilhelmus Patchin, Philetus Smith, Nathan Swift and Joel Patchin are all combinations of the first name of one candidate and the last name of another.
Nathan Smith received 88 votes as Mathan Smith, 2 votes as Wathan Smith, 1 vote as Nathaniel Smith and 1 vote as Nathan Snith.

Henry A. Townsend received 90 votes as Henry Townsend, 6 votes as Henry A. Towsed, 3 votes as Henry A. Towsend, 2 votes as Henry A. Towsend and 1 vote each as Henry D. Townsend, Henry H. Townsend, Henry A. Townsed and Henry A. Towsand.
Reuben Humphries received 1 vote each as Reuben Humphras, Reuben Humpry, Reuben Humphrin, Reuben Humpher, Reuben Hamphreys and Reuben Humphrear.
Philetus Swift received 1 vote as Philtus Swift and 1 vote as Philaster Swift.
Moss Kent received 48 votes as Moses Kent and 1 vote as Moss Rent.
Wilhelmus Mynderse received 4 votes as W. Mynderse, 2 votes as Wilhelmus Mynderse and 1 vote each as William Mynderse, Wilhel Mynders and Wylhelums Myderse.
Freegift Patchin received 1 vote as Freesift Patchin and 1 vote as Freegift Patcher.
Joel Thompson received 2 votes as Joel Thopson.

sub_unit.note: The Columbian (New York, NY) lists Reuben Humphries with 291 votes, Philetus Swift with 290 votes, Freegift Patchin with 356 votes and Joel Thompson with 358 votes.

sub_unit.name: Jefferson

The Columbian (New York, NY) of May 22 lists Nathan Smith with 1043 votes, and The Columbian (New York, NY) of May 22 and The Albany Register (Albany, NY) of May 15 both list Philetus Swift with 1040 votes.

sub_unit.name: Houndsfield
sub_unit.note: The Albany Register (Albany, NY) lists Henry A. Townsend with 4 votes.

The Columbian (New York, NY) lists Moss Kent with 110 votes which is likely an error because the sum for the towns would then be 1030 rather than the 1040 total it lists for the county (which is also the county total listen in The Albany Register (Albany, NY)).

sub_unit.name: Madison

sub_unit.name: Eaton
sub_unit.note: The Pilot and the Columbian Gazette both list Henry A. Townsend with 97 votes and Nathan Smith with 96 votes, but these are likely errors because the totals they list for the county match the totals listed in The Columbian (New York, NY), which lists Henry A. Townsend with 96 and Nathan Smith 97 votes in Eaton.

sub_unit.name: Jerusalem

sub_unit.name: Snell
sub_unit.note: The votes for Philetus Swift were written as "One Hundred and Sixty Four" but recorded in figures as 163 and listed as 163 in newspapers. The later number was used in the Official Returns, even though it was incorrect, as only fully written returns were to be submiited.

sub_unit.name: Sodus
sub_unit.note: The Geneva Gazette (Geneva, NY) lists Reuben Humphreys with 73 votes but this is clearly a misprint.

sub_unit.name: Otsego
sub_unit.note: Henry A. Townsend received 52 votes as Henry Townsend and 3 votes as Henry A. Towsend.
Reuben Humphries received 1 vote as Reuben Hamphreys.
Wilhelmus Mynderse received 1 vote as Wylhelums Myderse.

The Otsego Herald (Cooperstown, NY), Cooperstown Federalist (Cooperstown, NY) and Columbian Gazette (Utica, NY) with one exception all list Moss Kent, Freegift Patchin, Joel Thompson and Wilhelmus Mynderse with 1552, 1547, 1549 and 1549 total votes for the county, respectively, because they did not include the 93 votes they each received in Plainfield. The exception is the Cooperstown Federalist (Cooperstown, NY), which listed Freegift Patchin with 1537 total votes rather than 1547.

sub_unit.name: Plainfield
sub_unit.note: The Otsego Herald (Cooperstown, NY) of May 5 and Cooperstown Federalist (Cooperstown, NY) of May 5 list Moss Kent, Freegift Patchin, Joel Thompson and Wilhelmus Mynderse without votes in Plainfield although there are indications that they actually received 93 votes each that were not reported in the newspapers. The Columbian Gazette (Utica, NY) of May 22 does not list town results individually but lists the same county totals as are listed in the Otsego Herald (Cooperstown, NY).
